Class CheckingAccount

  • java.lang.Object
    • cscd210Classes.CheckingAccount

  • public class CheckingAccount
extends java.lang.Object
    A class representing a basic checking account. The checking account can't be created with a balance less than 100
    NOTE:
    All parameters must be passed as final including equals, You are required to use this. through out this class

      • deposit

        public void deposit(double amt)
        The deposit method allows for the class level balance to be changed. After the amount being passed in is verified to be > 0 then this.setBalance is called passing the current class level bal + the amt being deposited
        Parameters:
        amt - Representing the amount to be deposited.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the amt being passed in is <=0

      • withdrawal

        public void withdrawal(double amt)
        The withdrawal method allows for the class level balance to be changed. After the amount being passed in is verified to be > 0 then this.setBalance is called passing the current class level bal - the amt being deposited. If the amt being withdrawn is greater than the balance then nothing happens.
        Parameters:
        amt - Representing the amount to be withdrawn.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the amt being passed in is <=0
